    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "can u explain the math behind that a bit more? like how specifically is the interest calculated each month and why does it feel like it's eating up most of my money before it even touches the principal?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Interest is calculated monthly using the remaining principal balance multiplied by the annual interest rate, divided by 12. This calculation determines the interest charge for that specific month. Since the interest is calculated on the outstanding balance, and the principal is very high at the start, the interest amount itself is large, thus consuming a greater share of your payment before the remainder can chip away at the principal.",
