    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like money is disappearing into a black hole or something. it's frustrating because it feels like there's this hidden force working against me every time I make a payment. is there any way to avoid that \"eating away\" effect or is it just how all these loans are designed?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the design of amortizing loans inherently prioritizes interest early on, you can accelerate principal reduction by making extra, one-time payments directly applied to the principal. If you can afford it, increasing your monthly payment or making lump-sum payments will reduce the outstanding balance faster. By lowering the balance, you lower the base on which future interest is calculated, effectively minimizing that \"eating away\" effect over time.",
